Bootstrap for i.i.d. data.frames

Source: R/shared_bootstrap.R
bootstrap_variance.data.frame.Rd

Bootstrap for i.i.d. data.frames

Usage

# S3 method for class 'data.frame'
bootstrap_variance(
  data,
  estimator_func,
  point_estimate,
  bootstrap_reps = 500,
  ...
)

Arguments

data

a `data.frame` or a `survey.design`.

estimator_func

function that returns an S3 result object; the primary estimate is extracted via `$estimate` and convergence via `$converged`.

point_estimate

numeric; point estimate used for some survey variance formulas.

bootstrap_reps

integer; number of resamples.

...

passed through to `estimator_func`.

Value

a list with `se`, `variance`, and the vector of `replicates`.
